title: Here's What Happened at Taylor Swift’s Alleged Only Performance of 2017 - Taylor Swift Performed at DirecTV's Super Saturday Night Concert
text: A photo posted by Taylor Swift Updates (@taylorswift.updates) on Feb 4, 2017 at 9:53pm PST Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Now, Taylor obviously left the possibility open that she'll do more shows this year, but since she decided not to release an album last fall, she doesn't have a reason to embark on a big tour any time soon. But, if this does turn out to be Taylor's only show in 2017, she made it count. The setlist was packed with her biggest hits—mostly from 1989, sure, but also with some fan favorite throwbacks like "Love Story" and "You Belong With Me." — Taylor Swift News (@TSwiftNZ) February 5, 2017 Taylor also made a couple of performance debuts during the show. She performed "Better Man," the breakup anthem she penned for Little Big Town, for the first time ever.
